WEBVTT

00:00.162 --> 00:03.146
Okay, well, so good to be together this morning.

00:03.206 --> 00:05.289
So good to celebrate together this morning.

00:05.309 --> 00:07.812
I really am very and online.

00:08.273 --> 00:11.397
And true confession, I'm a big Blue Jay fan.

00:12.358 --> 00:18.026
And so I went to bed and I was like, man, I'm kind of bummed about the Blue Jays.

00:18.066 --> 00:20.289
There's part of me was like, man, I'm kind of bummed about the Blue Jays.

00:21.330 --> 00:27.138
But then I thought to myself, well, man, tomorrow I get to celebrate something even bigger than the Blue Jays.

00:27.298 --> 00:30.002
All that God has done with our four of them initiative.

00:30.178 --> 00:33.403
And talk about what it's going to mean to bring it home in the next eight weeks.

00:33.503 --> 00:36.086
And this is something we can actually bring home.

00:36.327 --> 00:39.591
And so I'm really excited to share with you today.

00:39.651 --> 00:48.283
If you weren't with us 18 months ago, we kicked off a brand new initiative called for them.

00:48.444 --> 00:53.010
And we thought, man, what would it mean to reach more people across

00:53.122 --> 01:17.729
Simcoe County and we said man because there are so many people who matter to us in fact This is why we started this church if you don't know that we we started Connects us to search for and celebrate people being found by Jesus and we saw what if we spent the next 20 months this was 18 months ago the next 20 months Making more space for them in our hearts making more space for them in our facilities.

01:17.849 --> 01:18.930
What might that be?

01:19.138 --> 01:19.799
look like.

01:19.979 --> 01:26.407
And the focus of it was Luke 15, which has kind of turned out to be a theme chapter for our church for the whole year.

01:26.988 --> 01:28.790
And it says this in one part of it.

01:29.331 --> 01:32.815
Jesus talks about a lost sheep, a lost coin, a lost son.

01:32.935 --> 01:34.497
And then he says, count on it.

01:34.718 --> 01:43.168
There's more joy in heaven over one sinner's rescued life than over 99 good people in need of no rescue.

01:43.328 --> 01:45.691
And this is Winston, who was baptized recently.

01:46.092 --> 01:47.794
Another picture of someone

01:47.906 --> 01:55.514
whose life was rescued, someone who found Jesus, someone who would say, hey, my life has been changed over the course of the last year.

01:55.654 --> 01:58.738
And we have seen this time and time again.

01:58.798 --> 02:00.580
I mean, how about Katie's story today?

02:00.600 --> 02:01.361
Can we thank Katie?

02:01.821 --> 02:03.123
Yeah, we're so excited.

02:06.486 --> 02:09.309
We're so excited for what God has done in her life.

02:09.570 --> 02:13.714
And one of the places we said, hey, we want to create more space.

02:13.826 --> 02:15.648
was at our Aurelia facility.

02:15.668 --> 02:22.555
We opened a brand new facility in Aurelia a year ago, and we did a Hello Aurelia initiative with it.

02:22.975 --> 02:31.143
And I don't know if you caught that in her story, but she says this, she says, but then all of a sudden I started getting cards left at my door that said, Hello Aurelia.

02:31.623 --> 02:36.708
And I remember sitting on my couch thinking, Katie, this is a sign you need to go to church.

02:36.728 --> 02:42.514
And over the course for them, as we open that facility, we have volunteers,

02:42.626 --> 02:54.304
who would hand out thousands of flyers, go to different neighborhoods again and again and again, saying, man, we want to invite everybody in a room to come and everyone to have an opportunity to meet Jesus.

02:54.665 --> 03:00.614
And Winston's story and Katie's story are just two examples of so many stories.

03:00.734 --> 03:10.770
In fact, I often say to people, I wish you had the opportunity to sit in my seat to hear all of the stories that I get to hear, and I don't even hear all of them,

03:10.882 --> 03:13.885
But my goal today is to share a couple of those with you.

03:14.245 --> 03:17.589
And my goal today is for you to see the difference that you're making.

03:17.629 --> 03:25.077
That if you're a part of making for them happen, if you financially invested in for them, lives are being changed.

03:25.457 --> 03:26.798
People are meeting Jesus.

03:27.018 --> 03:31.003
It's been incredible to see what has happened so far.

03:31.323 --> 03:33.565
And I wanna give you a glimpse of this today.

03:33.585 --> 03:38.290
And then I wanna give you an update on kind of what's coming for the next eight weeks.

03:38.402 --> 03:42.046
and then give you an update kind of on what's coming next year.

03:42.106 --> 03:46.471
And all of this is something that you're making possible for God to work.

03:46.591 --> 03:51.277
And so if you have invested in the for them initiative financially, I just want to say thank you.

03:51.437 --> 03:53.019
Thank you for your generosity.

03:53.459 --> 03:57.444
Man, God's writing so many stories because of your generosity.

03:57.504 --> 03:59.506
Generosity turned into transformation.

03:59.526 --> 04:00.748
It really is amazing.

04:01.268 --> 04:02.770
Now, if you remember,

04:02.850 --> 04:06.614
Our goal at the beginning of four then, we said, man, everyone matters there.

04:06.634 --> 04:16.065
450,000 people across Simcoe County, and I always put a dot below and above, because I know some people come from both ends of the county as well.

04:16.085 --> 04:24.014
450,000 plus people, and only 4% of them would find themselves in church on a Sunday morning.

04:24.575 --> 04:25.837
And we want to change that.

04:26.037 --> 04:27.058
It's that simple.

04:27.202 --> 04:28.083
We want to change that.

04:28.103 --> 04:30.728
We want to see more people meet Jesus.

04:30.808 --> 04:32.671
More people's lives changed by Jesus.

04:32.931 --> 04:36.817
More of these people found the hope that many of us have found.

04:37.538 --> 04:41.144
And the thing about this number is it's not just a number.

04:41.164 --> 04:44.490
It's not a number you just put on the wall somewhere and you say, well, that's our goal.

04:44.510 --> 04:45.391
It's our corporate goal.

04:45.671 --> 04:46.994
It's not like that at all.

04:48.195 --> 04:49.177
It's not just a mission.

04:49.217 --> 04:54.866
It's something personal because here throughout Simcoe County are people you know and people I know.

04:55.202 --> 04:56.283
It's your neighbors.

04:56.604 --> 04:57.525
It's your friends.

04:57.866 --> 04:59.868
It's the people who live down the street from you.

05:00.309 --> 05:02.091
It's the people where you shop.

05:02.191 --> 05:03.173
It's your colleagues.

05:03.213 --> 05:04.054
It's all of these people.

05:04.074 --> 05:04.695
It's your kids.

05:04.735 --> 05:05.416
It's your parents.

05:05.716 --> 05:09.201
I mean, these are real people and every one of these people matter.

05:10.382 --> 05:17.311
And we said, man, what would it mean if we said, let's invest in reaching more of those people?

05:17.632 --> 05:20.416
What if we really had the heartbeat that Jesus had?

05:20.956 --> 05:25.202
When he said, man, I left the 99 sheep to go after the one.

05:25.762 --> 05:28.186
And how have we done so far?

05:28.246 --> 05:29.128
What does this look like?

05:29.669 --> 05:31.892
What has happened in 18 months?

05:32.513 --> 05:36.821
And men, Katie's stories happen, Winston's stories happen, so many stories have happened.

05:36.841 --> 05:43.973
But to just kind of give you an overarching glimpse of what happened, you're not going to believe this.

05:43.993 --> 05:46.858
It has been an unbelievable 18 months.

05:46.998 --> 05:49.002
And here's what you've been a part of.

05:49.082 --> 05:51.666
Here's what you've helped make happen.

05:51.746 --> 05:58.858
You've been a part of seeing our real location increase by 49% in weekly attendance.

05:59.218 --> 06:00.440
That is a ton of people.

06:00.521 --> 06:01.182
Absolutely.

06:03.125 --> 06:07.412
And many of you who are seeing me right now in a real year, you weren't here 18 months ago.

06:07.452 --> 06:08.794
You weren't with us 18 months ago.

06:09.075 --> 06:10.297
Your life has been changed.

06:10.337 --> 06:12.040
Your life has been transformed.

06:12.060 --> 06:13.142
Many of you have met Jesus.

06:13.162 --> 06:14.223
Some of you are on the journey.

06:14.243 --> 06:15.826
You're asking questions.

06:15.906 --> 06:16.707
sure you believe.

06:16.727 --> 06:17.408
And that's awesome.

06:17.428 --> 06:18.810
We're really, really glad you're here.

06:19.110 --> 06:24.717
And we've, you've been a part of growing by 31% overall in weekly attendance across Kinexis.

06:24.777 --> 06:26.079
I mean, here's the thing.

06:26.099 --> 06:35.831
When we opened the facility in Aurelia, what we weren't prepared for was that the growth would increase in berry, that we are already growing and we just started growing faster.

06:35.971 --> 06:43.540
And so it's been amazing to see friends and family and neighbors invited and exploring and asking questions.

06:44.621 --> 06:45.202
And

06:45.314 --> 06:49.320
When it comes to transformation and people are on the journey, we've seen a lot of that too.

06:49.581 --> 06:50.702
Here's what you've been a part of.

06:52.145 --> 06:57.593
You've been a part of baptizing 95 people in the last 18 months as followers of Jesus.

06:57.613 --> 07:01.820
20 of them got baptized last Friday, which was amazing.

07:02.281 --> 07:03.262
Yeah, absolutely.

07:06.327 --> 07:13.298
Okay, well, after today it's 96, actually 96, thanks to Katie today, so that's even better.

07:13.410 --> 07:20.421
And then you've been a part of hosting 525 spiritually curious adults at Alpha.

07:21.162 --> 07:26.892
Alpha is an environment for people who have questions about faith, who will ask them questions of the Bible and want to explore who Jesus is.

07:27.533 --> 07:30.898
And in 18 months, 525

07:31.202 --> 07:31.563
people.

07:31.643 --> 07:40.596
In fact, the one that we currently have 190 people in Alpha, crossbarium, and they kept texting me saying, we're going to have to move to a different room.

07:40.616 --> 07:41.838
We're going to have to move to a different room.

07:41.858 --> 07:47.125
And now they're running them in the auditorium just to make space for everybody, which is incredible to see.

07:47.606 --> 07:51.993
People searching, people asking questions, people saying, hey, show me what the Bible means.

07:52.233 --> 07:53.595
I've got questions about Jesus.

07:53.875 --> 07:55.377
How is this relevant to my life?

07:55.498 --> 07:58.482
How do I know this is real?

07:58.658 --> 08:07.131
We kind of look at a couple of high water mark Sundays, like we'll look at things like Christmas Eve or Easter to kind of say, hey, how wide are we reaching?

08:07.151 --> 08:10.936
How many people are we actually having the opportunity to share the hope of Jesus with?

08:11.457 --> 08:13.160
And I just want to give you a glimpse of that.

08:14.081 --> 08:23.215
You've been a part of welcoming 3,955 first time guests in the last 18 months, almost 4,000 people who walked through the door.

08:23.295 --> 08:26.099
Yeah.

08:27.121 --> 08:27.922
And hosting

08:28.034 --> 08:34.805
3,251 people at Christmas Eve and about 3,600 people on Easter weekend.

08:34.825 --> 08:39.632
And so it's been amazing to see these are opportunities for people to hear the hope of Jesus.

08:40.493 --> 08:46.122
But the thing, we look at those and it's important that we look at them because every single number matters.

08:46.142 --> 08:47.304
That's why you need numbers.

08:47.344 --> 08:49.988
You need numbers because every single person matters.

08:50.048 --> 08:52.552
But they are actual people.

08:54.054 --> 08:55.236
In every one of them, they're people.

08:55.276 --> 08:56.338
They matter to you.

08:56.962 --> 08:58.043
And they mattered to us.

08:59.005 --> 09:00.947
That the people that matter to you mattered to us.

09:01.648 --> 09:07.175
The neighbor you're praying for, the parent you're praying for, the kid you're praying for, the colleague you're praying for.

09:07.215 --> 09:08.216
They mattered to us.

09:09.178 --> 09:12.001
And they mattered to all of us in the rooms that we're sitting in right now.

09:12.822 --> 09:14.725
And most of all, they mattered to God.

09:15.646 --> 09:17.228
And he sees them.

09:18.389 --> 09:25.298
And as we're kind of looking a little bit at story today, I wanted to show you one more story because sometimes

09:25.730 --> 09:31.296
It's important to hear a story that we get real close up and really get to see what happened in someone's life.

09:31.976 --> 09:35.740
And today, I want you to see Nikki and Taylor's story.

09:35.840 --> 09:41.866
Nikki and Taylor have recently, have been attending in the last year, are a really a location.

09:41.906 --> 09:51.616
And there was no really a location when we were in the movie theater before, but since we've opened that location, we met Katie who you met this morning, and we've also met Nikki and Taylor.

09:52.036 --> 09:53.938
And I want to give you a chance to get up close.

09:54.114 --> 09:55.175
and just hear their story.

09:55.396 --> 09:55.936
Check this out.

09:58.379 --> 10:01.603
Hi, my name's Taylor, and this is my gorgeous wife, Nikki.

10:03.406 --> 10:09.393
We've been married for about eight years, and we have two beautiful kids, Leila and Benny.

10:09.433 --> 10:12.457
Leila is almost seven, Benny is three.

10:12.517 --> 10:19.666
We landed here in Aurelio when we bought our first house, and we've lived up here for

10:19.874 --> 10:20.815
about almost seven years.

10:21.095 --> 10:25.380
Before we ended up at Connectsys, we actually were faced with a great deal of loss.

10:26.321 --> 10:31.226
We lost Taylor's grandparents kind of back to back within about six months of each other.

10:31.266 --> 10:34.530
And I had a really close friend actually commit suicide.

10:34.830 --> 10:41.698
We felt kind of lost and like we just didn't really know where to go and who to turn to.

10:41.798 --> 10:46.483
We have great family and friends, but it just felt like we were kind of missing something.

10:47.084 --> 10:49.106
My grandparents had passed away

10:49.282 --> 10:54.569
And I felt like with my family, I kind of had to be strong enough for everyone.

10:54.789 --> 10:57.933
And I didn't really get to process the loss.

10:58.433 --> 11:00.256
I never grew up going to church.

11:00.556 --> 11:01.938
So this was all very new to me.

11:02.078 --> 11:04.441
We had kind of spoke a little bit about it.

11:04.481 --> 11:07.344
And then Layla kind of was also asking some questions.

11:07.364 --> 11:11.870
We would drive past a cemetery that she would ask, you know, what is that?

11:11.910 --> 11:12.871
And we would explain it.

11:12.951 --> 11:16.976
And then she would ask, can we go to heaven to see these people?

11:17.116 --> 11:18.418
And to be honest, like,

11:18.594 --> 11:19.695
I didn't know how to answer it.

11:19.816 --> 11:20.777
We both didn't know how.

11:20.797 --> 11:20.877
Yes.

11:27.426 --> 11:32.232
We had seen the flags at the theater a bunch of times driving to Costco.

11:32.713 --> 11:34.495
I had heard about Conexis and Barry.

11:34.535 --> 11:39.883
I think I looked it up and you were just about to move to Four King.

11:40.103 --> 11:44.048
And so we decided to wait until the first opening at Four King.

11:44.108 --> 11:48.434
For the first Sunday coming, I didn't know what to expect.

11:48.610 --> 11:50.092
I'm not really one to dress up.

11:51.093 --> 11:53.257
So I didn't want to have to not be myself.

11:53.357 --> 11:55.139
I didn't want to put on a suit and a tie.

11:55.440 --> 12:04.212
That's not me on the day today, and I don't want to have to sell myself to people, essentially, I didn't even know.

12:04.232 --> 12:08.137
As soon as we came in for the first time, everyone just made you feel so welcome.

12:08.638 --> 12:11.462
Instead of saying nice to meet you, it was nice to see you.

12:11.782 --> 12:17.170
I felt literally like I knew everyone for years within 30 seconds of talking to them.

12:17.442 --> 12:20.106
We really related to the first service.

12:20.366 --> 12:23.330
It just felt like at that time, we needed to hear that message.

12:23.390 --> 12:27.316
And for me, that was enough of a sign to be like, we're supposed to be here.

12:27.336 --> 12:31.662
I remember we left and we were like, whoa, that was made for us.

12:32.343 --> 12:33.765
And so we came back the next time.

12:34.166 --> 12:37.030
And I remember Christine remembering our names.

12:37.270 --> 12:40.194
And I was like, whoa, that's huge.

12:40.374 --> 12:43.058
It's crazy that she remembers our names.

12:46.050 --> 12:56.502
our lives have been changed by Kinexis and so I can't thank anyone who helped this open up more than I can.

12:56.522 --> 13:00.226
I used to be very anxious, one of the most anxious people.

13:03.270 --> 13:13.682
And I have really combated that and have found some peace in my life and that's been huge.

13:14.210 --> 13:16.693
I had a guy at work actually telling me the other day.

13:16.893 --> 13:21.198
He said that he could tell that I was doing more than just attending on a Sunday.

13:21.939 --> 13:23.781
And I was like, like, what do you mean by that?

13:24.021 --> 13:35.895
The way that you carry yourself and the way this how calm you are and how you conduct yourself on hard situations.

13:35.915 --> 13:42.322
I just think that by following some of the stuff in scripture, it just

13:43.042 --> 13:46.445
makes you want to be better and be the best that you can.

13:46.886 --> 13:52.411
I recently got baptized and I help with Alpha as a host or a helper.

13:54.453 --> 13:58.717
I help out on Sundays with the E team out in the parking lot.

13:59.318 --> 14:01.300
I am a captain when I'm outside.

14:01.580 --> 14:02.822
The boys and I, we just have fun.

14:03.823 --> 14:08.707
Thank you to anyone that made this building happen.

14:09.288 --> 14:11.410
I don't know if we would have gotten to the theater

14:11.522 --> 14:19.715
I don't know if that would have been our spot, knowing that this building was opening and it was right at the perfect time for us.

14:20.156 --> 14:24.142
This facility was just so, so nice to walk into.

14:24.703 --> 14:28.649
You could tell that people had put like a lot of hard work into making it what it is.

14:29.250 --> 14:34.418
So for anyone, I would just say thank you for that, for giving us a spot, a church to call home.

14:45.506 --> 14:46.047
So good.

14:46.107 --> 14:49.311
And we appreciate Nikki and Taylor sharing their story.

14:49.551 --> 14:52.675
And man, I just want to say thank you.

14:52.715 --> 14:56.179
I'm just doing my very, very best in the short time.

14:56.260 --> 15:01.406
I have to say, you have made a huge difference if you've chosen to be a part of this.

15:01.566 --> 15:03.749
And we're so, so blown away.

15:03.809 --> 15:10.217
The other thing that's happened over the last 18 months, that we talked about at the beginning.

15:10.638 --> 15:14.002
But we've seen just grow exponentially.

15:14.306 --> 15:16.389
is how hungry people are.

15:17.331 --> 15:19.735
How hungry people are for hope.

15:19.755 --> 15:25.805
People like Nikki and Taylor who we saw today, how hungry they are to know more of Jesus.

15:25.885 --> 15:34.639
And we've seen people who have come to the front here, I would Sunday after Sunday saying, I want a Bible, I want to read a Bible.

15:34.779 --> 15:36.842
I've got questions about the Bible.

15:36.883 --> 15:39.026
There are so many Sundays

15:39.202 --> 15:41.946
where I meet people and they say, hey, show me how to read it.

15:42.106 --> 15:43.047
What does it look like?

15:43.208 --> 15:44.069
Where do I start?

15:44.229 --> 15:44.970
Where do I begin?

15:45.371 --> 15:47.594
What does this look like for me?

15:47.634 --> 16:05.379
And it really has been blown me away how over the course of the last 18 months, over the course of the last 18 months, I think our neighbors, I know our neighbors, our friends, the people around us are hungrier for hope than they've ever been before.

16:05.720 --> 16:07.282
It really is true.

16:07.650 --> 16:13.576
And I can't tell you how many people I meet who would say, actually invited somebody to church the other day.

16:13.596 --> 16:14.777
And you know what they said to me?

16:15.257 --> 16:17.840
I've always wanted to go, but nobody ever invited me.

16:19.441 --> 16:21.283
It's not that they're not interested.

16:21.303 --> 16:23.225
It's that they don't think they're welcome.

16:24.186 --> 16:28.089
And the question is, what if we were the kind of people who invited them?

16:28.109 --> 16:29.210
And what does it look like?

16:29.491 --> 16:33.635
How do we respond in a culture that's hungry for the hope of Jesus?

16:34.095 --> 16:37.298
Because the people around us are hungry than I've ever

16:37.378 --> 16:42.144
seen before it is an unbelievable time to be in ministry.

16:42.745 --> 16:47.452
And what I want to do today is I want to look very briefly at Acts 8.

16:48.633 --> 16:57.285
And in Acts 8, we're going to say, we're going to see an opportunity that somebody has to interact with someone who is spiritually hungry.

16:57.605 --> 17:00.930
And when we see them interact, it's actually going to create a model for us.

17:01.250 --> 17:04.114
It's going to help us to understand and inspire us

17:04.194 --> 17:10.721
What does it mean for us to continue to be for them in a hungry culture, a spiritually hungry culture?

17:11.282 --> 17:15.206
And this is what happens in Acts chapter eight, verse 26.

17:15.386 --> 17:24.276
It says, as for Philip, an angel of the Lord said to him, goes south down the desert road that runs from Jerusalem to Gaza.

17:24.316 --> 17:32.946
So Philip is out there preaching and all of a sudden he'd get this angel, Lord shows up and says, you gotta go down this road from Jerusalem to Gaza and says, so Philip started out

17:33.122 --> 17:41.150
And he met the treasurer of Ethiopia, a eunuch of great authority under Candake, the queen of Ethiopia.

17:41.170 --> 17:47.397
Now, if you don't know what a eunuch is, many of you will, but if you don't know, usually castrated as a child.

17:47.837 --> 17:59.890
And a eunuch was somebody who would be brought into your kingdom, in your home, into your government, because you would trust them, because there was someone who wouldn't end up kind of

18:00.002 --> 18:04.707
cheating with one of your wives or having a child with one of your wives.

18:04.727 --> 18:06.249
It was somebody that you could trust.

18:06.289 --> 18:10.393
They wouldn't be building their own kingdom because they don't have any family to hand it to.

18:11.094 --> 18:12.575
And so you would trust a eunuch.

18:12.596 --> 18:15.859
So that's why you see it's a eunuch of great authority.

18:16.700 --> 18:23.808
And it said the eunuch had gone down to Jerusalem to worship and he was now returning.

18:23.908 --> 18:26.130
Now the interesting thing is this eunuch

18:26.274 --> 18:35.363
goes down, he's not Jewish, but he goes to Jerusalem, and he wants to worship there, and he's not gonna be welcome in the temple because he's a eunuch.

18:35.383 --> 18:37.405
On one hand, he has all of this authority.

18:37.445 --> 18:39.928
On the other hand, he's a total outcast.

18:40.248 --> 18:43.151
They wouldn't let him into the inner part of the temple.

18:43.191 --> 18:45.393
He would have to stay outside, but still he went.

18:45.914 --> 18:52.120
And it says, seated in his carriage, he was a reading aloud from the book of the prophet Isaiah.

18:52.180 --> 18:54.482
This guy's actually reading scripture.

18:54.626 --> 18:57.170
in his carriage as he's riding.

18:58.291 --> 19:05.983
And it says, the Holy Spirit said to Philip, go over and walk along beside the carriage.

19:06.924 --> 19:12.232
How do we continue to engage a culture that's hungry for Jesus?

19:12.953 --> 19:14.255
We listen to the Holy Spirit.

19:14.996 --> 19:18.021
If you're part of sacred homecoming, that was part of what it was all about.

19:18.522 --> 19:24.210
That we need to be the kind of people, the kind of church that's made up of people who listen to the Holy Spirit.

19:24.706 --> 19:35.920
When they go to their workplace, when they're sitting on the sidelines watching their kid play sports, when they're interacting with their neighbor, and they're listening to the Holy Spirit, who would you have me speak to?

19:36.200 --> 19:37.502
Who would you have me share with?

19:37.802 --> 19:39.384
Who would you have me invite to church?

19:39.564 --> 19:45.131
You have me sit down with and walk alongside with, who do you want me to get in the corner of?

19:45.211 --> 19:50.738
We need to be those kinds of people, because it's not that people aren't spiritually hungry.

19:51.479 --> 19:54.162
Often, it's that the Christians aren't spiritually aware.

19:54.946 --> 19:56.148
And what would it mean for you?

19:56.188 --> 19:59.392
And I had to say, come Holy Spirit, show me every day what it means.

19:59.673 --> 20:00.895
What does it mean for us as a church?

20:00.915 --> 20:04.179
We want to continue to lean into the power of the Holy Spirit.

20:05.661 --> 20:13.132
This is in Philip after hearing the Holy Spirit ran over and he hears the man reading from the prophet Isaiah.

20:13.953 --> 20:15.776
He says, man, I hear you reading the Bible.

20:15.816 --> 20:17.238
I hear you trying to figure it out.

20:17.619 --> 20:19.041
This is our culture right now.

20:19.782 --> 20:22.866
People are seeing like the sales of Bibles right now.

20:22.978 --> 20:25.501
It's unreal how many Bibles are selling on Amazon.

20:26.182 --> 20:34.953
And the number of Bibles that we're giving away, the number of people who are curious, the number of people who are like, I had somebody say, I came to Jesus on TikTok.

20:34.973 --> 20:47.168
You know, I was on there and they were talking about the Bible and I started leaning in, I started watching more videos and meant it's a time when people are hungry and we need to continue to look for people who are seeking and searching.

20:47.188 --> 20:51.794
And you see here he says, Philip sits, sits a long time says, do you understand what you're reading?

20:52.642 --> 20:56.906
Now, the interesting thing about Philip is he's just walking on the road.

20:57.166 --> 21:01.571
This guy goes by, he's reading scripture, and Philip could say, well, you know what?

21:01.591 --> 21:02.031
I'm busy.

21:02.972 --> 21:04.073
You know what?

21:04.093 --> 21:05.935
I'm actually going to a different place.

21:05.955 --> 21:10.159
I'm actually going to where God called me down from Gaza, Jerusalem.

21:10.179 --> 21:11.220
I'm going down this way.

21:11.240 --> 21:12.442
I'm on this road.

21:12.462 --> 21:13.603
I don't have the time for this.

21:15.384 --> 21:16.245
But that's not what Philip does.

21:16.265 --> 21:21.010
He says, you know, I'm going to make the time that the Holy Spirit says is an opportunity here.

21:21.538 --> 21:23.984
The Holy Spirit says there's somebody who's searching here.

21:24.004 --> 21:25.668
There's somebody who's asking questions here.

21:27.151 --> 21:30.961
How do we continue to be for them in a culture when people are hungry?

21:31.221 --> 21:32.003
We make time.

21:32.584 --> 21:34.930
We make time for people who are looking for hope.

21:35.906 --> 21:37.748
That's what we're doing when it comes to Alpha.

21:37.768 --> 21:39.650
That's what we're doing when it comes to Sunday morning.

21:39.931 --> 21:44.356
We're continuing to make time for people to come and say, hey, you can belong.

21:44.416 --> 21:46.899
Even if you aren't sure you believe yet, come ask your questions.

21:47.219 --> 21:48.480
Come along with me to church.

21:48.881 --> 21:53.767
Like, I know I don't normally get up for the nine o'clock service, but I will for you.

21:53.827 --> 21:55.208
I'm gonna make time for you.

21:55.288 --> 21:56.690
Let's go together.

21:58.512 --> 22:00.274
And this is this demand replied.

22:00.994 --> 22:03.137
How can I unless someone instructs me?

22:03.177 --> 22:06.322
How can I understand this Bible unless someone teaches it to me?

22:07.424 --> 22:12.552
And so we urge Philip to come up into the carriage and to sit with him.

22:13.634 --> 22:14.916
Come sit alongside me.

22:15.778 --> 22:17.981
Come sit alongside me and show me.

22:19.043 --> 22:21.427
Come sit alongside me and answer my questions.

22:21.487 --> 22:24.191
Come sit alongside me and show me what the Bible means.

22:24.451 --> 22:28.658
Come sit alongside me and help me understand what it is to follow him.

22:30.338 --> 22:38.247
in a country in an area where we live in our neighborhoods where people are hungry, we make room.

22:38.988 --> 22:42.952
We make room to sit with people who are asking questions.

22:44.053 --> 22:45.675
We wanna make room in our services.

22:45.715 --> 22:46.956
We wanna make room in Alpha.

22:46.976 --> 22:48.638
We wanna make room in our small groups.

22:48.658 --> 22:57.268
We wanna make room in our lives to sit with people who are asking questions and say, hey, let's have a conversation about faith.

22:57.288 --> 22:59.410
Let's have a conversation about who Jesus is.

23:00.706 --> 23:05.132
And it says, the passage of scripture that Eunuch had been reading was this.

23:05.613 --> 23:10.220
And he's reading out of Isaiah and it says, he was led like a sheep to the slaughter.

23:10.620 --> 23:14.726
And as a lamb is silent before the shearers, he did not open his mouth.

23:14.746 --> 23:20.795
This is a prophecy, hundreds of years before Jesus even came about his death on the cross.

23:21.736 --> 23:25.842
And then it says this, he was humiliated and received no justice.

23:26.523 --> 23:28.466
Who can speak of his descendants?

23:28.738 --> 23:30.680
for his life was taken from the earth.

23:31.741 --> 23:36.267
It's so interesting that you have this eunuch who's so interested in this passage.

23:36.487 --> 23:36.767
Why?

23:38.149 --> 23:40.151
Because he was humiliated.

23:40.191 --> 23:42.714
He received no justice.

23:44.155 --> 23:46.839
And he was one who had no descendants to speak of.

23:48.661 --> 23:51.103
And he's engrossed in this passage of scripture.

23:51.143 --> 23:57.010
This is speaking right to me, he says, for his life was taken from the earth.

23:58.690 --> 24:01.132
And Philip is sitting alongside the eunuch.

24:02.093 --> 24:02.934
He's made time.

24:02.974 --> 24:04.836
He's made room in his life.

24:05.396 --> 24:06.778
He's listening to Holy Spirit.

24:07.719 --> 24:13.424
And it says, the eunuch asked Philip, tell me, was the prophet talking about himself?

24:13.804 --> 24:15.266
Or was he talking about someone else?

24:15.586 --> 24:16.727
Who was he talking about?

24:16.767 --> 24:23.674
And so beginning with this same scripture, Philip told him the good news about Jesus.

24:25.595 --> 24:28.338
The word gospel is another word for good news.

24:29.282 --> 24:30.584
He met him right where he was at.

24:31.205 --> 24:31.926
He made time.

24:31.967 --> 24:33.088
He made space.

24:33.429 --> 24:34.791
They opened the Bible together.

24:34.831 --> 24:39.519
And he made the good news of Jesus accessible to his new friend.

24:41.563 --> 24:43.185
And that's what we want to do.

24:43.206 --> 24:46.611
We want to make the gospel accessible to everyone we can.

24:47.693 --> 24:49.636
The truth of the gospel doesn't change.

24:50.358 --> 24:55.346
But man, we're so well positioned to share it with our entire community.

24:55.618 --> 24:57.159
We're so well positioned online.

24:57.200 --> 25:04.807
We're so well positioned in our rooms and we wanna continue to position ourselves to continue to share the hope of Jesus with so many people.

25:06.909 --> 25:07.750
And then it happens.

25:08.971 --> 25:15.077
It says, as they wrote along, they came to some water and the eunuch said, look, there's some water.

25:16.118 --> 25:17.599
Why can't I be baptized?

25:19.601 --> 25:24.786
And he ordered the carriage to stop and they went down into the water

25:25.090 --> 25:27.273
and Philip baptized him.

25:28.714 --> 25:33.500
Right in the carriage, the light bulb goes on for this guy.

25:35.062 --> 25:38.266
It's the moment that we as a church live for.

25:38.326 --> 25:52.242
The moment someone goes from wanting to see Jesus to the realization that Jesus already sees them, that he's seen them all along, and he desperately wants to have a relationship with him.

25:54.050 --> 25:55.511
And he's so excited about it.

25:56.052 --> 26:00.596
He's like, just, just baptize me right there in that dirty river or wherever that puddle is.

26:00.636 --> 26:01.417
Like, let's do it.

26:03.559 --> 26:08.004
His life has been radically changed because somebody made room for him.

26:10.106 --> 26:12.088
Somebody made room for him in their life.

26:14.270 --> 26:22.578
And that's what for them is always, always been about making room for people in our lives and in our hearts and in our church.

26:23.970 --> 26:27.154
We talked about two opportunities to be for them.

26:27.495 --> 26:33.202
And we talked about creating room in our church for people because we continue to have full services.

26:33.382 --> 26:36.306
And now 18 months later, even more full services.

26:38.028 --> 26:42.194
And we want to continue to make room for people that when our friends come, we want to have space for them.

26:42.234 --> 26:43.355
We want to have seats for them.

26:43.395 --> 26:44.797
We want to have opportunities for them.

26:45.298 --> 26:48.562
And then we want to create room, more room in our hearts for people.

26:49.442 --> 26:58.652
but this just can't be something that we give to and go, okay, well, like I gave financially and now add some seats, but I'm not really interested in reaching people.

26:58.952 --> 27:00.233
That's not really in my heart.

27:00.273 --> 27:02.596
No, we want our hearts changed and transformed.

27:04.538 --> 27:15.890
And so what I want to do today is for the rest of our time, I want to give you an update as to where things are at because we had four hard initiatives that we wanted to go after

27:16.130 --> 27:22.439
that we wanted to financially fuel in order to be for them, in order to create more room, just like Philip did.

27:23.581 --> 27:26.565
And so for them, where are we at currently?

27:26.605 --> 27:28.187
And what's next?

27:28.407 --> 27:29.168
I want to update you.

27:29.209 --> 27:30.210
You guys ready for an update?

27:30.851 --> 27:31.392
Okay, good.

27:31.472 --> 27:32.433
I hope earlier you're ready.

27:32.453 --> 27:32.834
You can hear me.

27:32.854 --> 27:33.695
We're ready for an update.

27:33.935 --> 27:40.765
Now, initiative number one, when it comes to making more room, open a permanent facility in downtown Aurelia.

27:40.925 --> 27:41.726
We have done that.

27:42.227 --> 27:43.208
We celebrate today.

27:43.228 --> 27:44.370
It's amazing.

27:47.746 --> 27:49.308
Here's the thing we didn't expect.

27:50.469 --> 27:56.916
We have officially been in that building for 12 months and we've just launched an 1158 service to make more space.

27:56.957 --> 27:58.518
So it has grown so quickly.

27:58.558 --> 28:00.501
So we're so excited about that.

28:01.942 --> 28:03.724
So it's been incredible to see.

28:03.824 --> 28:04.585
It is amazing.

28:04.705 --> 28:05.727
It is incredible to see.

28:05.787 --> 28:10.472
The next two initiatives I'm going to update you on together.

28:10.592 --> 28:12.274
Now the first one was to

28:12.450 --> 28:15.714
Open a second worship auditorium and bury for growth.

28:15.814 --> 28:20.540
This room has been quite full at most of our services and we can't make this room any bigger.

28:20.580 --> 28:32.956
And so we said we're going to open a second auditorium in another part of the building, which will have live music and a live host and then the teaching on the screen that we were going to add that second auditorium to make more room for our friends.

28:33.737 --> 28:37.522
And in addition to that, we were going to open a new next generation

28:37.730 --> 28:43.296
student space and we said let's create more space for them and here's actually what the original plan looked like.

28:44.697 --> 28:52.124
This is our current student space that we were going to make a second auditorium and then we're going to move the students over here into this unit.

28:52.865 --> 29:00.273
Now we're really excited about it but there were a couple of challenges with the plan and I want to give you an update on it that we're really excited about.

29:01.634 --> 29:05.778
The challenges were adding this auditorium of about 150

29:05.922 --> 29:11.910
We've already realized that, oh man, that actually might be too small at the rate that we're growing.

29:12.771 --> 29:22.944
Second of all, the student space is gonna be a little smaller, but the biggest challenge, and many of you came to me about this, was like, Jeff, you're not making the lobby any bigger.

29:23.505 --> 29:27.570
How are you gonna add a whole other auditorium and have the same lobby?

29:28.031 --> 29:33.778
Like, I like these people, but not that much that I wanna stand like right against them.

29:33.890 --> 29:38.494
And some of the women were like, you know, there's a lineup in the washroom already after the service, right?

29:39.355 --> 29:41.417
And like you're not adding any washrooms.

29:42.799 --> 29:50.366
This past August, just a couple of months ago, I'm excited to let you know that we're approached by the landlord of this facility.

29:51.006 --> 29:55.050
And they said to us, hey, another unit next to you is coming available.

29:55.651 --> 29:58.473
And if you lease it, you've got 10 days to jump on it.

29:59.014 --> 30:03.218
And if you jump on it, you can grab it and you can lease that unit as well.

30:03.426 --> 30:04.428
And so that's what we did.

30:04.848 --> 30:06.571
And so, yeah.

30:10.296 --> 30:11.578
So you want to see the new plan?

30:11.719 --> 30:12.540
No, there's a new plan.

30:12.840 --> 30:14.703
So this is what the new plan looks like.

30:15.965 --> 30:21.173
So what this is going to mean is our students are actually going to stay here because it's a better room for them.

30:21.594 --> 30:29.746
And we're going to make that room bigger, take out some of the interior walls, renovate that whole space, make this an even better space than they would have had for them.

30:30.082 --> 30:33.265
and then move the second auditorium over to this end.

30:33.706 --> 30:38.811
Now with these two units, this will now see 250 to 275 people.

30:39.773 --> 30:44.938
In addition to that, we're gonna blow this open and extend the lobby all the way across.

30:45.799 --> 30:50.284
So you can still stand close to people you like, but you don't have to stand close to everybody.

30:50.724 --> 30:55.890
So it'll go all the way across, and then we're gonna add some washrooms down here at this end.

30:56.130 --> 31:00.034
And then we've accounted for kid space, realized we need a little bit more in elementary.

31:00.475 --> 31:03.758
So they had 50 kids in their large group room, which is not made for that.

31:04.199 --> 31:07.623
And so we're going to expand this space as well in order to make it bigger.

31:08.183 --> 31:16.092
And so we'll have enough space for students, enough space for kids, and a second auditorium on this side that seats 250 to 275 people.

31:16.573 --> 31:17.634
In fact, I made a list.

31:17.714 --> 31:18.515
What's bigger and better?

31:18.535 --> 31:19.476
Here's the list.

31:19.496 --> 31:21.298
A larger second auditorium.

31:21.474 --> 31:27.020
a new expanded lobby, more washrooms, more student space, and an expanded up-street large group room.

31:27.160 --> 31:27.681
How about that?

31:28.201 --> 31:28.502
Yeah.

31:33.427 --> 31:43.018
So what we've done is we've actually been able to secure some financing so we can get started on this right away, this additional space, and all of it in 2026.

31:43.318 --> 31:50.226
And so we're excited to see all of that move forward this coming year, the student space we're aiming for the spring,

31:50.466 --> 31:57.153
and the second auditorium in lobby were aiming for this coming summer because nobody wants to do construction around Christmas.

31:57.373 --> 31:59.396
So we definitely want to get it done.

31:59.436 --> 32:03.580
So we're super excited about more room to invite your friends.

32:04.261 --> 32:08.025
Now there was a fourth initiative that I'm also excited to share with you about.

32:08.425 --> 32:12.810
It was to multiply our influence with a church multiplication director.

32:13.431 --> 32:16.274
Some of you know that we have a network of churches

32:16.514 --> 32:18.658
that we blow wind in their sails.

32:18.678 --> 32:22.004
They're all churches, Canadian churches that want to reach people.

32:22.324 --> 32:28.055
We resource them, we coach them, we get behind them, and it's been amazing to see all that God has done.

32:28.095 --> 32:30.218
Actually, I'll throw them up here where they all are.

32:30.298 --> 32:31.420
Most of them are in the East here.

32:31.461 --> 32:33.023
It's been amazing to see what God has done.

32:33.083 --> 32:39.936
We've invested in 14 churches, and we're thrilled with the progress as they've grown, as they've reached more people where they are.

32:40.657 --> 32:41.298
But we

32:41.410 --> 32:43.213
also are a part of a network.

32:43.233 --> 32:45.757
We're a part of the irresistible church network.

32:45.777 --> 32:50.323
We have been out of North Point Community Church, Andy Stanley's Church, who you may have heard preach here.

32:50.984 --> 32:55.912
We've been a part of their network since the very beginning, and they have been an incredible gift to us.

32:56.653 --> 32:59.678
And what's happened is their network has really grown.

33:00.198 --> 33:07.650
They were originally North American, and now they're launching global networks, and they're at 250 churches.

33:08.771 --> 33:10.514
And they came to us

33:10.818 --> 33:12.901
and said, hey, we have Canadian churches.

33:13.442 --> 33:14.783
You have Canadian churches.

33:15.344 --> 33:20.251
What if together we approached those churches and launched a brand new network together?

33:21.072 --> 33:26.719
And so they've said, hey, what would it mean for you to launch the irresistible church network, Canada?

33:27.200 --> 33:30.204
And they're willing to resource us and get behind us.

33:30.364 --> 33:33.449
And actually, if you want to get a picture of where their church is there, they're the blue ones.

33:34.430 --> 33:40.498
And there are 94 communities of 30,000 or more across Canada.

33:40.706 --> 33:46.796
And we would love to see an outward-facing church that's looking to reach people in every single one.

33:47.558 --> 33:52.546
And so what we're going to do is we're going to launch the Irresistible Church Network Canada.

33:52.646 --> 33:54.309
It's going to be its own organization.

33:54.369 --> 34:01.621
So our little experiment with our 14 churches is we're going to come its own thing with its own board and its own staff.

34:02.082 --> 34:04.306
And we're going to turn the temperature up

34:04.546 --> 34:09.411
on reaching unchurched people across the entire country, which is going to be incredible to see.

34:09.871 --> 34:11.232
And we're so excited about it.

34:11.353 --> 34:20.682
So you're going to see that rolling out over the course of the next 12 to 24 months, that entire network.

34:21.242 --> 34:23.364
And we're meeting with them now, which is amazing.

34:23.484 --> 34:27.288
So now, some of you are like, OK, this is awesome.

34:27.348 --> 34:31.672
But there was a financial goal to make all this happen where we are on the financial goal.

34:31.772 --> 34:33.554
And so I want to update you on that.

34:33.698 --> 34:40.047
The financial goal was we had 2.95 million that you pledged by the end of 2025.

34:40.107 --> 34:45.335
This coming December, we're eight weeks away above and beyond regular giving.

34:46.016 --> 34:48.659
And you've been amazing in fulfilling your pledges.

34:48.820 --> 34:50.442
And so thank you for that.

34:50.943 --> 34:55.910
We are currently at 2.587 in fulfilled pledges.

34:56.030 --> 35:01.778
So we're just 363,000 away in the last eight weeks.

35:01.986 --> 35:05.491
from hitting our 2.95 million target.

35:05.691 --> 35:09.536
And so if you're here today, and you're wanting, hey, what's next?

35:09.836 --> 35:19.529
And I want to tell you what's next, because if you didn't think your giving makes a difference, I hope you see today, none of this happens without the investment of people sitting in the seats like you.

35:20.450 --> 35:25.757
And second of all, if you didn't think your giving would make a difference, clearly it really would.

35:25.777 --> 35:27.259
We're so close to the goal.

35:27.279 --> 35:29.202
363,000.

35:29.282 --> 35:31.024
away from the finish line.

35:31.184 --> 35:32.465
And so here's what's next.

35:33.006 --> 35:35.388
First of all, complete your for them pledge.

35:35.488 --> 35:40.313
If you haven't yet finished your completion of your pledge, complete it before the end of the year.

35:40.673 --> 35:48.701
Leslie and I are at the tail end of ours, and we had to make some different financial changes to make it happen, but God has showed up for us financially.

35:48.721 --> 35:50.943
It's been an amazing journey for us spiritually.

35:50.983 --> 35:57.970
And so we're looking to complete our pledge by the end of the year, and if you've pledged, we would encourage you to do the same.

35:58.498 --> 36:03.725
Second of all, prayerfully, give to for them to help us finish strong.

36:04.306 --> 36:07.270
So maybe you're here today and you missed out on this.

36:07.791 --> 36:08.933
You would say, well, I wasn't here.

36:08.993 --> 36:09.974
Many of you weren't here.

36:10.255 --> 36:11.316
You were the for them.

36:12.037 --> 36:13.359
And now you're here in the seats.

36:14.180 --> 36:16.203
And now it's time for you to do for them.

36:16.924 --> 36:20.349
And so it's time for you to jump in financially and be a part of this.

36:20.609 --> 36:21.410
There's still time.

36:21.811 --> 36:26.898
If you go to the lobby, there's these brochures you can pick up if you're looking for more detail.

36:27.042 --> 36:30.447
you can go to connectstchurch.com slash four of them and jump in.

36:30.587 --> 36:34.233
If you missed out the first time, this is the time we need you to jump in.

36:34.694 --> 36:43.147
And if you're here today and you're like, well, I fulfilled my pledge, what more could you do to help us to get all the way to the 2.95 million?

36:43.487 --> 36:47.173
We're so close to being there, but it's gonna take all of us to make it happen.

36:47.533 --> 36:51.519
You can go to the website on the screen there and there isn't pledging anymore.

36:51.539 --> 36:55.826
There's only eight weeks left and just make your financial gift by your end.

36:56.034 --> 36:58.337
and we're excited to see what God is going to do.

36:58.417 --> 36:58.957
Is that clear?

36:59.017 --> 37:00.479
Okay, good, good.

37:00.599 --> 37:07.487
So I want to remind you, it's about making room in our facilities, but it's also about making room in our hearts, right?

37:07.527 --> 37:10.370
It's not just about buildings.

37:10.390 --> 37:17.638
In some senses, the buildings are just tools to see the people across Simcoe County reach, the people who matter to you and matter to me.

37:18.679 --> 37:22.904
And I really want to ask you the question, who are you for?

37:22.964 --> 37:25.106
That is the other question to be asked here.

37:25.826 --> 37:27.287
